This application uses a JWT-based authentication system with
access tokens, refresh tokens, and Redis session storage for
enhanced security and scalability.

Overview

The authentication flow consists of:

User registration with email activation

Login with access & refresh token generation

Secure cookie-based token storage

Redis-backed session management

Role-based authorization

Token refresh mechanism

Logout with session invalidation

Token Architecture

1️⃣ Access Token

Short-lived (e.g., 5 minutes)

Stored in HTTP-only cookie

Used to access protected routes

Signed with ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET

2️⃣ Refresh Token

Longer-lived (e.g., 20 minutes)

Stored in HTTP-only cookie

Used to generate new access tokens

Signed with REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET

Security Features

HTTP-only cookies (prevents XSS token theft)

Role-based authorization

Server-side session validation

Token expiration enforcement

Email-based account activation

Secure environment variable secrets

Tech Used

Node.js

Express

JWT (jsonwebtoken)

Redis (ioredis)

MongoDB (Mongoose)

bcrypt (password hashing)

LMS Backend

This is the backend API for a Learning Management System (LMS). It provides all the core functionalities for managing users, courses, categories, layouts, notifications, orders, and analytics. Built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB, it’s designed to be secure, scalable, and easy to integrate with a frontend application.

Features

User Management

Register, login, and authenticate users

Role-based access control (admin, instructor, student)

Profile management

Course Management

Create, update, and delete courses

Assign courses to categories

Track course progress and enrollment

Layout & CMS

Manage homepage layouts including banners, FAQs, and categories

Dynamic content updates via admin panel

Notifications

Push notifications to users when new courses or updates are added

Orders & Payments

Manage course purchases

Track order history

Analytics

Track course enrollments, revenue, and user activity

Generate monthly and yearly reports

Cloud Integration

Upload and manage images with Cloudinary

Secure file storage for banners and course content

Caching

Redis caching for faster data access

Error Handling & Validation

Centralized error handler

Input validation for all APIs

Security

JWT-based authentication

Role-based authorization

Secure password storage with hashing

Tech Stack

Backend: Node.js, Express

Database: MongoDB, Mongoose

Authentication: JWT

File Storage: Cloudinary

Caching: Redis

Validation & Security: express-validator, bcrypt

Dev Tools: TypeScript, ESLint, Prettier
